Package: stringi
Version: 1.4.7
Date: 2020-08-24
Title: Character String Processing Facilities
Description: Fast, portable, consistent, correct, and convenient character
    string/text/natural language processing in every locale and any native encoding.
    Owing to the use of the 'ICU' (International Components for Unicode)
    library, the package provides 'R' users with platform-independent functions
    known to 'Java', 'Perl', 'Python', 'PHP', and 'Ruby' programmers. Available
    features include: pattern searching (e.g., with 'Java'-like regular
    expressions or the 'Unicode' collation algorithm), random string generation,
    case mapping, string transliteration, concatenation, sorting, padding,
    wrapping, Unicode normalisation, date-time formatting and parsing,
    and many more.
URL: http://stringi.gagolewski.com/
    http://site.icu-project.org/
    http://www.unicode.org/
BugReports: http://github.com/gagolews/stringi/issues
SystemRequirements: ICU4C (>= 55, optional)
Type: Package
Depends:
    R (>= 2.14)
Imports:
    tools,
    utils,
    stats
